UML:TaggedValue.value: Citizen Science Profile of O&M v3
Metadata specific to citizen science sampling campaigns. Most likely it needs to be extended with campaign specific metadata. Alternatively, additional metadata can be provided by reference.
Comments or notes about the Event. See http://rs.tdwg.org/dwc/terms/#eventRemarks for further details.

UML:TaggedValue.value: The class NamedValue provides for a generic soft-typed parameter value. NamedValue shall support two attributes.

The attribute name:GenericName shall indicate the meaning of the named value. Its value should be taken from a well-governed source if possible.
EXAMPLES When used as the value of an Observation:;parameter, the name might take values like ‘procedureOperator’, ‘detectionLimit’, ‘amplifierGain’, ‘samplingDepth’.
The attribute value:Any shall provide the value. The type Any should be substituted by a suitable concrete type, such as CI_ResponsibleParty or Measure.
multiplicity needs to be changed to 0..1 to allow promoting information to the collection model, but this is currently in conflict with the observation core model.

The CitizenProcess consists of the person(s) that has executed and recorded the observation and any number of assets and sensors used.
Additional tools used for that observation that are not sensors, e.g. color cards to identify the color of an observed property.

The person that is executed the observation and has published the result. According to the codelist provided by ISO/TC211/19115 the citizen scientist has the role of "originator". For further details, see here.
The CitizenScienceProcess includes all citizen science specific aspects such as citizen identification and sensor descriptions.
References the SamplingProtocol used. Will be provided by reference because sampling protocols can have any level of complexity.

UML:TaggedValue.value: The campaign process is used if aggregated information about a sampling campaign is provided. The campaign process allows conserving all information about the citizens that contributed to the campaign.
Used if the result is a swe:DataRecord.

UML:TaggedValue.value: The CitizenScienceResult makes use of SweCommon in combination with SKOS for elemement definitions to allow for arbitrary result value types.

Used if the result includes more than one result entry and all result entries are of the same structure. Result values will be provided in specialized compact encodings (TextBlock, XML, or BinaryEncoding).
